ex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dto1665702580637.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dto1665702580637.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dto1665702580637.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dto1665702580637\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Window Type (WindowType)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Window property of a form that determines the type of window used to display the form. One of: <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">Normal</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Dialog</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Primary</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Secondary</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Contained</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Popup</code>\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dto1665702580637__section_w4305ab1b5b1_w4306ab1b5_w4307ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">Normal</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Fully-customizable window; all other window properties can be set.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Dialog</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Modal, non-resizable window used to display forms as dialog boxes. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eoe1665702580713.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eoe1665702580713.html\" title=\"A dialog window is a modal, non-resizable window used to display forms as dialog boxes, which is typically used to display or retrieve a limited amount of information. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Dialog.\">Dialog Window</a>.\n                                          </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Primary</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Non-modal window that cannot be moved outside the application shell. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"omf1665702580793.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/omf1665702580793.html\" title=\"A primary window displays the form in a non-modal window that cannot be moved outside the application shell. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Dialog.\">Primary Window</a>.\n                                          </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Secondary</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Window that can be displayed outside the application shell. It usually contains information that is dependent on an object in the primary window. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sgs1665702580867.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgs1665702580867.html\" title=\"A secondary window can be displayed or moved outside the bounds of the application shell. It is usually associated with a primary window, and is used to contain information that is dependent on an object in the primary window. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Secondary.\">Secondary Window</a>.\n                                          </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Contained</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Secondary, non-modal window that cannot be resized. It enables the form to be displayed in a Tab widget or Form Container widget. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fue1665702580943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fue1665702580943.html\" title=\"A contained form is a secondary, non-modal window that is displayed in a form container widget, or as a tab in a tab widget. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Contained.\">Contained Form</a>.\n                                          </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Popup</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dto1665702580637__table_d11669e1_d11670e1_d11671e1__entry__2\">\n Secondary, non-modal window that can pop up or drop down from a specified position in a widget. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rhe1665702581016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rhe1665702581016.html\" title=\"A popup window displays a form in a secondary window that is anchored to a field. The position of the popup window is configurable, so that it can be displayed outside or inside the boundaries of its parent field.\">Popup Window</a>.\n                                          </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dto1665702580637__section_jlb_lzw_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464157e248\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dto1665702580637__p_d100118e1_d100119e1_d100120e1\">The value of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span>\n            property determines the other properties that can be set. If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window\n               Type</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">Normal</code>, all other window properties can be set.\n            Other values restrict the availability of other window properties.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"dto1665702580637__note_yy1_mzw_swb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> To change the default settings for other window\n            elements, such as the active title bar, active window border, and so on, you can use the\n            Microsoft Windows Control Panel or the Unix XResources.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dto1665702580637__section_a3j_mzw_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464157e269\">Setting Window Type in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dto1665702580637__p_d100124e1_d100125e1_d100126e1\">When creating a component instance of a form using\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span>, it is possible to specify <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n               windowtype=</code>popup as one of the component instance properties. Setting\n            windowtype to a value other than <code class=\"ph codeph\">popup</code> is not accepted and generated\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-1410</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dto1665702580637__p_d100127e1_d100128e1_d100129e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ryt1665702577808.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryt1665702577808.html\" title=\"Creates a new instance of a component.\">newinstance</a>.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dto1665702580637__ul_mfz_r1x_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eoe1665702580713.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eoe1665702580713.html\" title=\"A dialog window is a modal, non-resizable window used to display forms as dialog boxes, which is typically used to display or retrieve a limited amount of information. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Dialog.\">Dialog Window</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"omf1665702580793.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/omf1665702580793.html\" title=\"A primary window displays the form in a non-modal window that cannot be moved outside the application shell. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Dialog.\">Primary Window</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sgs1665702580867.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgs1665702580867.html\" title=\"A secondary window can be displayed or moved outside the bounds of the application shell. It is usually associated with a primary window, and is used to contain information that is dependent on an object in the primary window. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Secondary.\">Secondary Window</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fue1665702580943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fue1665702580943.html\" title=\"A contained form is a secondary, non-modal window that is displayed in a form container widget, or as a tab in a tab widget. It is defined by setting the window property Window Type to Contained.\">Contained Form</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rhe1665702581016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rhe1665702581016.html\" title=\"A popup window displays a form in a secondary window that is anchored to a field. The position of the popup window is configurable, so that it can be displayed outside or inside the boundaries of its parent field.\">Popup Window</a></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tnl1665702834887.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Defining Single Document Interface (SDI) Behavior</a><p>By default, Uniface forms use a Multiple Document Interface (MDI), but it is possible to set window properties to force Single Document Interface (SDI) behavior.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Window Type (WindowType) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Window Type (WindowType) Window property of a form that determines the type of window used to display the form. One of: Normal | Dialog | Primary | Secondary | Contained | Popup Value Description Normal Fully-customizable window; all other window properties can be set. Dialog Modal, non-resizable window used to display forms as dialog boxes. For more information, see Dialog Window . Primary Non-modal window that cannot be moved outside the application shell. For more information, see Primary Window . Secondary Window that can be displayed outside the application shell. It usually contains information that is dependent on an object in the primary window. For more information, see Secondary Window . Contained Secondary, non-modal window that cannot be resized. It enables the form to be displayed in a Tab widget or Form Container widget. For more information, see Contained Form . Popup Secondary, non-modal window that can pop up or drop down from a specified position in a widget. For more information, see Popup Window . Description The value of the Window Type property determines the other properties that can be set. If the Window Type is Normal , all other window properties can be set. Other values restrict the availability of other window properties. Note: To change the default settings for other window elements, such as the active title bar, active window border, and so on, you can use the Microsoft Windows Control Panel or the Unix XResources. Setting Window Type in ProcScript When creating a component instance of a form using newinstance , it is possible to specify windowtype= popup as one of the component instance properties. Setting windowtype to a value other than popup is not accepted and generated $procerror -1410 . For more information, see newinstance . Dialog Window Primary Window Secondary Window Contained Form Popup Window Related Links Defining Single Document Interface (SDI) Behavior By default, Uniface forms use a Multiple Document Interface (MDI), but it is possible to set window properties to force Single Document Interface (SDI) behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}